Key Match Events: CJ McCollum scored 38 points to lead the Pelicans past the 76ers 123-115
Pre-Game Insights: Zion Williamson was suspended for one game for a violation of team policies
Joel Embiid missed the game due to a sprained left foot
Post-Match Reflections: No post-match reflections provided in the article
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Pelicans snapped a two-game losing streak and won for only the third time since Dec. 7
The 76ers are 15-21 and hoping at this point just to make the play-in tournament
Others: Jordan Hawkins helped the Pelicans with 21 points
Dejounte Murray had 17 points and 10 rebounds for the Pelicans
Paul George had 25 points and 11 rebounds for the Sixers
Tyrese Maxey had 30 points and 12 assists
Kelly Oubre Jr. scored 21 points for the Sixers
